<p>I want to launch a new site that doesn't have a subdomain - no "www".</p>  <p>All my sites are https.</p>  <p>Previously, I would have used the following code to redirect to www:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;rule name="Redirect to www subdomain" stopProcessing="true"&gt;           &lt;match url="(.*)" /&gt;           &lt;conditions&gt;             &lt;add input="{HTTP_HOST}" pattern="^(www\.)(.*)$" negate="true" /&gt;           &lt;/conditions&gt;           &lt;action type="Redirect" url="https://www.{HTTP_HOST}/{R:0}" redirectType="Permanent"/&gt;         &lt;/rule&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I've been trying to work out how to create the opposite rule (from www), but I get redirection errors. Here's the code I have so far:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;rule name="Remove www subdomain" stopProcessing="true"&gt;   &lt;match url="(.*)" /&gt;   &lt;conditions&gt;     &lt;add input="{HTTP_HOST}" pattern="*://www.*" /&gt;   &lt;/conditions&gt;   &lt;action type="Redirect" url="https://{HTTP_HOST}/{R:0}" redirectType="Permanent" /&gt; &lt;/rule&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Any advice appreciated.</p>